annotation.TEXT: Nuts. Flandre didn't quite make it there. Expect a lot of pause menu restarts.
Of course, if this Extra level is designed around Marisa's abilities, I'd better be Marisa, not Nitori.
Whatever. I'll just hit the checkpoint then use the pause menu to warp Flandre to me.
Seriously, why are we sloppier than we should be now?

Wow, that was a thing! BTW, I later tried this by myself lots of times, and while I could reach the goal, I just could not quite get the book in time. If I do so later, I'll upload it. Anyway, next time, more torture! To be continued... Ze!
This level is specially designed for me. The others couldn't advance.
Nuts. The opponent activated a fatal trap card.
Welp, we lost already, due to the little delay there.
Hello, and welcome back to Urapani! So, last time, we beat the game! And, I talked with Flandre about which Extra level we should start with, and we decided on 6-1... or ?-1. Whatever you call it.
Bah, accidentally ran off the edge of the platform.
Wow, Flandre made that with three straight mana bombs.
...That is... if the player that remains above actually makes it to the other side...
You're meant to drop one of Marisa's bombs down here to hit at least one of these timer switches, but this is totally cheesable with multiple players.
Pfft... We've probably already lost this run. We really can't waste even one second, or we'll likely run out of time at the end.
ARGH!!! So close! That platform with the dozen 1-ups on it is the goal platform, of course.
And, I'll tell you right now-- it's right behind the goal, requiring us to use hidden blocks to jump over the goal to reach it.
Whoa, that baton pass! Okay, now rush to get the book, quick!
There's no way both players can make this next jump, as there's only one F. But, the trail of point items down there leads to a 1-up, so may as well grab that with the suicider.
I don't know why I tried mana bombing again there.
From full energy, you have just enough mana for one full tackle and one mana bomb.
And here, we just use team work, with one of us hitting the blue timer switch, while the other leaps for the blue platforms.
Argh! Flandre should've totally made it that time...
Okay, now in this area, look at the timer. It starts at only 35 seconds here! (I did notice this right away the first time we got here on the laggy runs.)
Flandre, what was that? Well, at least we reached the checkpoint. Anyway, there were no DCs, and we did make it to the goal on one attempt, but I just didn't want to keep the lag-filled recording.
And, it would help if I actually reached that F...
I forget if I mentioned this before, but an important thing to note here is that the F items instantly fill your energy as well as your health.
As such, we know practically the whole level, and have an idea on how to reach the book (even though we didn't actually grab it). Of course, that's not to say we won't still die a lot...
While attacking, you can move again by using jump or dash. â™ª
I sacrifice myself in order to summon Dark Magician Girl!
Well, that's how you get to the green platform, and then I like to take an intentional hit from the gray spikes in order to cheese my way past the red spikes using mercy invincibility.
Too bad it was all for naught.
Hmm... I think downward dashes are more efficient than trying to mana bomb them.
NOTE: If you're at 3 HP, you don't quite need to be 100% full-- Like 90% is enough. But, if you're at 2 HP, you DO need 100% mana to do both moves consecutively.
Huh, this seems to be a Marisa-themed level, but the game doesn't restrict you from bringing in other characters.
Even with teamwork, it's not easy. The non-sacrificial lamb has to not screw up.
D'oh! Flandre used two mana bombs in a row there, instead of using just one mana bomb along with a standard broom tackle.
However, even after we reach the goal platform, we won't quite be done yet, as there'll still be the book to grab.
Okay, enough derping. Let's actually start making respectable attempts again.
Now, truth be told, we've "unintentionally" scouted again. We had some major lag issues on previous attempts to play this level, and the recordings were less than adequate.
And, expect a lot of deaths, especially since there are too few resources for two players.
So, yeah. We really gotta book it, beginning with getting through these fairies efficiently.
The mana bomb uses slightly less energy, but doesn't propel you as far as a full broom tackle. It's necessary to know which skill(s) you need to use at times in order to make it.
